    <p> Today was a special day again, albeit from a not so nice occasion. Today unfortunately the last day had come on the Sam and I drove through New Zealand together. We were lucky again and dreamy weather paired with a really nice route along two huge lakes. </p>
    <p> We first had to look for the campsite for the night a little in Wanaka. We were already in the right street but doubted that there was more than a gravel road. It was only when another camper came towards us that it was clear that we were right. So far, the campsite has been the best. We got places with a fantastic view over the lake and on the mountains. </p>
    <p> After, emptying and filling the water tanks again, we decided to drive into the city with just one car and go out to eat there. After all, it is our last evening together. We found a pub with a view of the lake and treated ourselves to a good meal. </p>
  </div>
</div><div class="row margin-bottom-10">
