    <p> Since Sam has his birthday soon, I had a travel guide for the filming locations from the Lord of the Rings. So she can search and visit other locations on her route. The rest of the evening, we sat in the cars and told who wanted to do what the next few days and where the trip goes. </p>
    <p> The next morning it was time. Now our paths should separate indefinitely, since Sam has three months and I slowly have to make my way towards Christchurch. After more than two years of good friendship and countless weekend trips. We were on many mountains during that time and are all the more valleys. Have researched countless cities and regions by car and on foot. Machnal even by ship. Drove to Sligo to learn to ride on the beach, were in countless pubs and enjoyed the mostly Irish culture together. All of this should now be over for an indefinite time, since none of us know whether and where we will see each other again in life. I definitely hope that it won't take too long. </p>
